Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE are pleased to present 262-264 Glebe Point Road, Glebe.

262-264 Glebe Point Road offers a unique and significant residential conversion opportunity, allowing it to capitalise on Glebe's exclusive, high demand and strong performing residential market. 

The property is ideal for residential developers due to the ability to utilise the building's current improvements and expansive existing gross floor area. 

262-264 Glebe Point Road commands a premium corner location and consists of four storeys plus basement parking, with levels one to three designed around a centralised core. Additionally, the building includes a large 365sqm* rooftop which boasts views of the surrounding district and nearby Sydney CBD.

262-264 Glebe Point Road benefits from the following key attributes:

- Four storey building with basement parking and rooftop breakout space
- Significant conversion potential suitable for residential flat buildings
- Land area of 708sqm* with a gross floor area of 1,685sqm*
- Large floor to ceiling heights and generous light & ventilation
- Premium corner location commanding three street frontages
- Prime location just metres from Rozelle Bay, Jubilee Park,
shops and dining
- Direct light rail and bus services to Sydney CBD

The property will be sold via public auction on Friday, 12 June 2020 at 12.00pm.

*approximate

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE and McGees Property are pleased to present 48-64 Wentworth Park Road, Glebe. Located in one of the most vibrant inner city suburbs, the apartment block is a premium investment within walking distance of Sydney Harbour and Sydney CBD.

The historic building underwent a tasteful residential conversion in 2009 to 36 luxury apartments overlooking Wentworth Park and is situated metres from the Blackwattle Bay waterfront development. Each oversized apartment caters to a growing demand for city fringe living.

46  64 Wentworth Park Road, Glebe benefits from the following key attributes:
 36 oversized residential apartments:
-	16 x 1 bedroom apartments of 78sqm* (average)
-	19 x 2 bedroom apartments of 85sqm* (average)
-	1 x 3 bedroom apartment of 132sqm*
 Estimated gross income of $1,800,000 per annum*
 NLA of 3,000sqm*
 Land area of 1,105sqm*
 Three street frontages plus 23 secure car spaces accessed from rear lane
 Overlooking the leafy Wentworth Park and Racetrack
 Well positioned to take advantage of the $250 million transformation of Blackwattle Bay and the Sydney Fish Markets, which will commence at the end of 2018
 Opportunity to strata subdivide and sell down individually in a sought-after city fringe location
 250m* from Blackwattle Bay, 350m* to Glebe Light Rail Station and 1.3km* from the Sydney CBD
 Depreciation benefits from 2009 renovation relating to plant and equipment and capital works allowance

*Approximate
